snippet.textDisplay:
Microsoft is a software company and Sony is a hardware company. I’m sure Sony knows exactly what they are doing. They’ve learned from the mistakes of the PS3 and will continue to make a dominant console. Even the PS3 outsold the 360 over the generation of the 2 consoles.

If you know anything about restrictions/bottlenecks, you know they cause friction and heat. I’m extremely happy to hear the bottlenecks are being removed.

Also they’ve said that next gen consoles will allow you to remove the single player or MP part of the game if not in use. The 850 gb ssd may be plenty if you can choose what parts of the game you can keep.
snippet.textOriginal:
Microsoft is a software company and Sony is a hardware company.  I’m sure Sony knows exactly what they are doing.  They’ve learned from the mistakes of the PS3 and will continue to make a dominant console.  Even the PS3 outsold the 360 over the generation of the 2 consoles.   

If you know anything about restrictions/bottlenecks, you know they cause friction and heat.  I’m extremely happy to hear the bottlenecks are being removed.  

Also they’ve said that next gen consoles will allow you to remove the single player or MP part of the game if not in use.  The 850 gb ssd may be plenty if you can choose what parts of the game you can keep.
